♪ <i>Um, baby, wop-a dop-a doo-bah </i>♪

01:23.083 --> 01:26.875
Baloo, turn it down!

01:30.000 --> 01:33.250
[Becky] All right, Baloo. That's too much!

01:33.333 --> 01:35.417
Yeah, ain't it though.

01:35.500 --> 01:37.208
Glad you like it, Becky.

01:38.625 --> 01:40.500
No, Baloo. I meant...

01:40.583 --> 01:43.458
Thanks. I'd love to dance.

01:54.875 --> 01:55.959
Aah...

01:56.625 --> 02:00.333
Oh, not my daddy's record.

02:00.417 --> 02:01.875
[Kit] Aw, Baloo.

02:01.959 --> 02:03.709
That was your favorite song, too.

02:03.792 --> 02:06.709
I know. I've heard it a million times.

02:06.792 --> 02:09.208
Last copy in the world

02:09.291 --> 02:14.750
of "I Got Them Flat Broke Sticky Shoed
No Banana Boogie-woogie Blues"<i>.</i>

02:16.000 --> 02:19.000
Boy... ahem.

02:19.083 --> 02:20.625
Tough break.

02:22.333 --> 02:25.625
[Kit] Come on, Baloo.
The world's full of great tunes.

02:25.709 --> 02:29.250
No, Little Britches.
That song was special.

02:29.750 --> 02:34.208
[sighs]
I can still hear that bebopping beat.

02:34.291 --> 02:35.875
I hear it too. Look!

02:35.959 --> 02:39.542
[boogie-woogie plays]

02:39.625 --> 02:42.458
[Baloo] "Absolute last copy on Earth."

02:42.542 --> 02:45.583
Oh, man. My toes are tapping already.

02:45.667 --> 02:46.917
What's wrong?

02:47.792 --> 02:50.458
[Baloo] A hundred bucks.

02:51.375 --> 02:53.250
Nothing. <i>Nada.</i>

02:53.333 --> 02:54.667
Flat broke.

02:55.750 --> 02:59.166
Who'd be dumb enough to loan me
a hundred bucks?

03:03.125 --> 03:07.041
You want me to advance you $100?

03:07.125 --> 03:09.458
What's the money for, Baloo?

03:09.542 --> 03:14.000
Um, it's sort of for, uh, uh... record.

03:14.083 --> 03:16.208
What kind of a record?

03:16.291 --> 03:20.291
Well, it's a really, uh, classic record.

03:20.375 --> 03:21.875
Oh, that's different.

03:21.959 --> 03:24.542
I love classical music.

03:24.625 --> 03:28.375
[Baloo] Me, too.
Especially when it's got a beat.

03:28.458 --> 03:30.041
[Baloo scat singing]

03:31.083 --> 03:33.667
I knew it. It's that stupid banana song.

03:33.750 --> 03:34.959
No sale.

03:36.083 --> 03:37.166
You want money?

03:37.250 --> 03:38.667
Take a lesson from Kit.

03:38.750 --> 03:44.291
Not two minutes ago he was in here asking
if he could <i>earn </i> extra money by working.

03:44.375 --> 03:45.542
Work?

03:48.750 --> 03:50.917
Kid, what are you doing?

03:51.000 --> 03:53.667
Working's a fate worse than being broke.

03:54.083 --> 03:55.959
But look what I've made so far.

03:56.041 --> 03:58.583
A whole dollar. Wow!

03:58.667 --> 04:01.083
And I've got 49 more just like it.

04:01.166 --> 04:03.166
My entire life savings!

04:03.250 --> 04:04.709
Fifty bucks?

04:04.792 --> 04:08.166
Say, that's half
of what I need to buy my record.

04:08.250 --> 04:11.667
Kid, <i>this </i> is your lucky day.

04:11.750 --> 04:12.750
It is?

04:12.834 --> 04:15.000
Yup. Ol' Baloo's gonna teach you

04:15.083 --> 04:16.875
the easy way to make money.

04:16.959 --> 04:21.791
Now Baloo... If this is another one
of your screwball schemes...

04:21.875 --> 04:26.000
In fact, I'll double your money
if you let me keep anything extra.

04:26.083 --> 04:30.834
Of course I'll... need to borrow
your 50 bucks to get started.

04:30.917 --> 04:32.875
Baloo, no.

04:32.959 --> 04:35.250
Kid, trust me.

04:48.291 --> 04:50.542
[Baloo] Welcome to Moola-Boola, kid.

04:50.625 --> 04:53.375
[Baloo] Trading center
of the uncivilized world.

04:53.458 --> 04:57.417
[Baloo] Land of thrills,
adventure, and easy money.

04:57.500 --> 05:02.041
And with your bucks and my brains,
we're gonna clean up.

05:02.125 --> 05:03.125
How?

05:03.875 --> 05:05.250
[Baloo] Heh-heh, hey!

05:05.333 --> 05:06.709
Baloo!

05:06.792 --> 05:10.291
-[Bobo] All right, man.
-[Baloo] Long time no see, baby.

05:10.375 --> 05:11.792
[Baloo] You lookin' good.

05:11.875 --> 05:13.208
[Bobo] Good to see you, man.

05:13.291 --> 05:17.000
Bobo, I'd like you to meet my good friend
and financial advisor,

05:17.083 --> 05:18.250
Kit Cloudkicker.

05:18.333 --> 05:22.375
Hiya. Hiya doin' there.
Nice to meet you, kid. How are you, pal?

05:22.458 --> 05:23.500
Uh, hello.

05:23.583 --> 05:26.583
So, Bobo, babes. Lay the news on Balooz.

05:26.667 --> 05:28.875
I mean, give the buzz, cuz.

05:28.959 --> 05:31.125
Like where's the big time action?

05:31.208 --> 05:32.542
Well, my man.

05:32.625 --> 05:35.709
The big time action is, ahem...

05:37.208 --> 05:38.834
Right over there.

05:38.917 --> 05:41.166
In fact, that's the...

05:42.500 --> 05:44.500
Only action, but watch out, man.

05:44.583 --> 05:46.250
That plane belongs to...

05:46.375 --> 05:48.291
[Bobo] Trader Moe.

05:48.375 --> 05:51.709
[Bobo] If anybody tries to horn in
on his customers,

05:51.792 --> 05:56.375
they're gonna wind up in deep mango peel.

05:57.417 --> 05:59.917
You know what I, um, mean?

06:00.000 --> 06:01.834
Thanks for the info.

06:01.917 --> 06:02.917
Baloo!

06:03.166 --> 06:05.750
Now, kid, you got to spend
money to make money.

06:05.834 --> 06:07.125
Come on.

06:08.542 --> 06:09.625
Here it is, boys.

06:09.709 --> 06:13.500
The precious cargo
that's taken me three months to gather.

06:13.583 --> 06:15.417
Now be careful with it.

06:15.500 --> 06:17.333
Duh, we'll be careful.

06:17.417 --> 06:19.166
Oh, <i>ja</i>. Very careful.

06:20.458 --> 06:24.417
Gad! I'm surrounded by stupids!

06:25.917 --> 06:28.333
Yeah, I'm stupid.

06:28.333 --> 06:30.583
Yeah, me too. I'm good at stupid.

06:31.291 --> 06:32.291
<i>Ja.</i>

06:33.834 --> 06:35.542
[Rhino] Uh, boss...

06:35.625 --> 06:37.834
What's so special about a box?

06:37.917 --> 06:40.500
[Gorilla] Yeah. Why box so special, boss?

06:40.583 --> 06:43.500
It's what's <i>in </i> the box, you peachpits.

06:43.583 --> 06:45.417
We're taking that box up north.

06:45.500 --> 06:48.500
I'm gonna trade it for 10 big ones.

06:48.583 --> 06:50.000
Ten of them. Wow!

06:50.083 --> 06:51.834
Better than 9.

06:51.917 --> 06:53.166
I'm going to lunch.

06:53.250 --> 06:55.083
Watch that box.

06:55.959 --> 06:56.959
The box.

06:57.041 --> 06:58.834
<i>Ja, </i> I'm watching now.

06:59.750 --> 07:01.291
[Baloo] Ten big ones, huh?

07:01.375 --> 07:04.834
Little buddy. You're about to observe
a master at work.

07:05.667 --> 07:07.166
What are you looking at?

07:07.250 --> 07:10.709
-Uh, the box.
-Watching good, box.

07:11.000 --> 07:13.333
Oh and it looks fun, too.

07:13.417 --> 07:18.041
In fact it looks so fun,
I'll pay you to let me watch it.

07:18.125 --> 07:22.750
Uh-uh. The boss says he's gonna make
10 big ones off of this box.

07:22.834 --> 07:24.792
Oh, <i>ja</i>. Uh-huh, 10.

07:24.875 --> 07:26.375
[Baloo] OK, you talked me into it.

07:26.458 --> 07:27.458
Hey!

07:27.542 --> 07:28.917
Here's 20 big ones.

07:29.000 --> 07:33.083
Double what your boss was gonna make.
Will he be proud of you!

07:33.709 --> 07:34.667
OK.

07:34.750 --> 07:36.500
Oh, <i>ja</i>. Okey-dokey, fine.

07:40.333 --> 07:43.375
Um, where did you say your boss
taking this box?

07:43.458 --> 07:45.166
Duh, up north.

07:45.250 --> 07:47.125
Oh, what he said.

07:47.208 --> 07:48.875
Thanks.

07:51.417 --> 07:53.792
[Trader Moe] You sold <i>what?</i>

07:53.875 --> 07:55.083
Yeah, heh heh.

07:55.166 --> 07:57.000
We got 20 bucks.

07:57.083 --> 07:58.583
Ain't you proud of us?

07:58.667 --> 08:01.125
<i>Ja, </i> twice as much.

08:02.000 --> 08:03.500
You lugnuts!

08:03.583 --> 08:05.709
I meant 10,000 bucks!

08:05.792 --> 08:08.083
Do you have any idea what was in that box?

08:08.542 --> 08:09.625
Worms?

08:09.709 --> 08:10.792
[gong sounds]

08:10.875 --> 08:13.166
Cute little guys, aren't they?

08:13.250 --> 08:15.166
-Ee-ya!
-Ee-ya!

08:15.667 --> 08:18.083
Sorry, I meant cute big guys.

08:18.166 --> 08:20.583
Are you crazy?

08:20.667 --> 08:24.333
You spent my life savings
on a box of worms?

08:24.417 --> 08:25.750
Trust me.

08:25.834 --> 08:28.875
We're gonna make
big bucks off those worms.

08:28.959 --> 08:31.500
I just got to figure out how.

08:33.166 --> 08:37.750
[Kit] Aw, Baloo. You call this place
the road to easy money?

08:39.166 --> 08:41.792
It's all part of the plan.

08:43.041 --> 08:44.959
Are they part of the plan, too?

08:45.041 --> 08:48.458
Hmm, you not Trader Moe.

08:48.542 --> 08:51.959
No, but I've got your worms.

08:52.041 --> 08:55.542
[chanting]

09:01.375 --> 09:03.125
[worms] Eee-ha!

09:06.458 --> 09:09.375
Hmm, we have enough fish for whole winter.

09:09.458 --> 09:11.041
What you want for worms?

09:11.125 --> 09:12.792
Say, 100?

09:12.875 --> 09:15.834
A hundred!
Baloo, sorry I ever doubted you.

09:15.917 --> 09:18.041
Oh, it wasn't much.

09:18.125 --> 09:21.583
Not much? Hmm, OK, 200.

09:21.667 --> 09:22.959
Oh! Two hund--

09:23.041 --> 09:26.083
We'll take whatever you were
going to give Trader Moe.

09:26.166 --> 09:29.083
Ha-ha! You good trader.

09:29.166 --> 09:30.709
Drive hard bargain.

09:30.792 --> 09:33.083
Ok, you get...

09:34.000 --> 09:37.417
Sparky, the half-pint sled dog?

09:37.500 --> 09:40.875
Trust me, kid. He's worth big bucks in...

09:40.959 --> 09:43.542
Uh, where was Trader Moe going?

09:43.625 --> 09:45.041
Maswitch village.

09:45.125 --> 09:46.875
Where else they need dog?

09:46.959 --> 09:48.208
Right.

09:53.166 --> 09:57.542
[Trader Moe] They sold my worms
and took my Sparky?

09:57.625 --> 09:59.709
Gad! [babbling]

09:59.792 --> 10:00.750
[Trader Moe] Get 'em!

10:05.041 --> 10:06.917
I'm going to get those guys.

10:07.000 --> 10:09.625
Nobody outtrades Trader Moe.

10:09.709 --> 10:10.750
No--

10:25.041 --> 10:27.917
[Baloo] Now we wait for the locals
to rush out

10:28.000 --> 10:30.834
and pay us big bucks for ol' Sparky here.

10:30.917 --> 10:32.291
Uh, I think.

10:32.375 --> 10:37.041
Come on, Baloo. Who would want to buy
a dog in a cat heaven like this?

10:37.125 --> 10:41.083
[cats meowing]

10:41.750 --> 10:43.583
[growling]

10:43.667 --> 10:45.542
[barking]

10:45.625 --> 10:47.375
Sparky's gone bonkers!

10:47.458 --> 10:48.959
Hang on!

10:50.041 --> 10:51.959
[cats screeching]

10:53.500 --> 10:55.208
Bad, Sparky. Bad!

10:55.291 --> 10:56.667
Get back here.

11:00.750 --> 11:04.250
We better get out of here
before those cats' owners get back.

11:11.041 --> 11:13.125
This your dog?

11:13.208 --> 11:15.041
Gee, I don't know what got into him.

11:15.125 --> 11:17.875
He's not usually so spunky.

11:17.959 --> 11:21.750
Oh, how can we ever thank you?

11:21.834 --> 11:23.750
We can breathe again.

11:23.834 --> 11:25.625
[sneezes]

11:25.709 --> 11:28.083
We're allergic to cats, you know.

11:28.166 --> 11:30.792
Let's hear it for our heroes.

11:30.875 --> 11:34.375
Hooray! That's great!

11:34.458 --> 11:39.875
I suppose you wouldn't take
$500 in payment?

11:39.959 --> 11:41.792
Take it. Take it!

11:41.875 --> 11:46.000
Uh, we'll take whatever you were
going to give Trader Moe.

11:47.041 --> 11:49.709
[Kit] Ten dozen umbrellas!

11:49.792 --> 11:52.750
Ok, OK. I got it.

11:52.834 --> 11:55.750
We're going to sell them
in the rain forest, right?

11:55.834 --> 11:58.333
Wrong. In the desert.

11:58.417 --> 12:01.458
Ho-ho. Oh! Ha-ha.

12:13.291 --> 12:15.542
Oh!

12:15.625 --> 12:17.750
Those two beat me again!

12:17.834 --> 12:19.750
This is all your fault.

12:19.834 --> 12:23.250
If youse two was any stupider,
you'd fall off the world.

12:23.333 --> 12:25.667
Yeah, right off the world.

12:25.750 --> 12:28.000
<i>Ja</i>, right over the edge. Splat.

12:28.083 --> 12:29.667
[growling]

12:29.750 --> 12:32.333
Yow! Hey! Hey!

12:32.417 --> 12:35.959
Oh! Oh! Whoa!

12:46.375 --> 12:50.417
[Baloo] "Olympic diving competition"?
In the middle of the desert?

12:51.083 --> 12:53.125
The first guy to get a perfect 10

12:53.208 --> 12:57.208
marries the chief's daughter
and gets the royal inheritance.

12:57.291 --> 12:58.291
[audience applauds]

12:58.375 --> 13:00.500
[boing]

13:00.583 --> 13:04.125
[crowd cheering]

13:06.667 --> 13:08.750
[yawns]

13:08.834 --> 13:10.375
A two?

13:10.750 --> 13:12.750
I can beat that.

13:18.125 --> 13:19.125
What?

13:19.208 --> 13:20.792
3.5?

13:21.417 --> 13:23.208
What kind of joint is this?

13:23.291 --> 13:25.792
That was a 3.7 easy.

13:26.083 --> 13:29.166
We're finally one step ahead
of those guys.

13:29.250 --> 13:33.333
Now remember, I'm the chief
and youse two are my guards.

13:37.959 --> 13:40.291
We bring umbrellas to trade.

13:40.375 --> 13:43.792
Welcome to Mondo-Bobo,
youse two intruders.

13:43.875 --> 13:46.208
Uh, I mean traders. Yeah.

13:46.291 --> 13:49.542
We was going to fix
a feast in youse guys honors,

13:49.625 --> 13:54.041
but instead,
we fixed a plot in the local cemetery.

13:54.125 --> 13:55.375
Grab 'em, boys!

13:56.542 --> 13:57.750
Aah...

13:57.834 --> 13:59.542
-Trader Moe.
-Trader Moe.

14:05.208 --> 14:08.625
You didn't say the road
to easy money was straight down.

14:08.709 --> 14:11.709
Well, toss 'em over.

14:11.792 --> 14:14.750
Uh, yeah. Toss us over.

14:14.834 --> 14:15.875
What?

14:16.542 --> 14:19.417
Then <i>we'll </i> get to marry
the chief's daughter and get rich,

14:19.500 --> 14:21.667
and your boss won't.

14:21.750 --> 14:26.000
Uh, yeah! Boy, will he be sore at you!

14:26.792 --> 14:28.667
Sore at us? Oh-oh.

14:28.750 --> 14:30.417
What we should do?

14:30.500 --> 14:33.834
Well, since we're such nice guys,

14:33.917 --> 14:36.709
we'll let you throw
your boss over the cliff.

14:36.792 --> 14:39.000
But just this once, OK?

14:39.083 --> 14:43.375
I said toss 'em over the cl--
What do you-- Aagh!

14:43.458 --> 14:47.500
Hey, you banana peels!

14:47.583 --> 14:48.834
Ooh-hoo-hoo.

14:50.875 --> 14:54.500
Oh, no. Aagh...

14:54.583 --> 14:56.083
[crowd cheering]

14:56.166 --> 14:57.417
What was that?

14:57.500 --> 14:58.875
Hey, wow!

15:01.500 --> 15:02.375
Aagh!

15:02.458 --> 15:04.792
Watch it! Look out!

15:04.875 --> 15:06.333
Out of the way!

15:10.834 --> 15:12.750
Quick! Your boss is losing.

15:12.834 --> 15:14.875
Get down and help him win.

15:14.959 --> 15:18.750
-[Rhino] Yeah. We're coming, boss.
-[Gorilla] Here comes us.

15:18.834 --> 15:21.458
[both] We'll help you.

15:21.542 --> 15:23.834
Don't help me. Don't help me!

15:23.917 --> 15:26.125
[crowd] Ew!

15:29.375 --> 15:34.208
[crowd cheering]

15:35.917 --> 15:38.250
Hoo-hoo-hoo. You saved me.

15:38.333 --> 15:39.792
Found hubby for daughter,

15:39.875 --> 15:43.125
and, best of all, brought umbrellas.

15:43.208 --> 15:47.083
Now divers break fall, not legs.

15:47.166 --> 15:48.834
Aw, 'twas nothing.

15:48.917 --> 15:50.959
Bumper shoots worth big bucks.

15:51.041 --> 15:53.250
Say, a thousand?

15:53.333 --> 15:54.166
What?

15:54.250 --> 15:56.291
Well now, don't want to be greedy

15:56.375 --> 16:00.250
but how's about we take what you were
gonna give Trader Moe.

16:00.333 --> 16:01.834
Oh, no!

16:02.583 --> 16:04.709
[Kit] Six clamshells?

16:04.834 --> 16:06.917
Oh. Don't tell me.

16:07.000 --> 16:10.333
Oh, you gonna use 'em
as fish communicators in Bambeezee.

16:10.417 --> 16:12.959
Oh, no, no, wait. I've got it.

16:13.041 --> 16:14.375
You've got it wrong, kid.

16:14.458 --> 16:16.625
What did I tell you about easy money?

16:16.709 --> 16:20.250
In Moola-Boola,
six clamshells are worth...

16:20.333 --> 16:22.875
[Kit] $10,000!

16:22.959 --> 16:26.000
Ha-ha! I told you to trust me.

16:26.083 --> 16:27.583
We're rich, rich!

16:27.667 --> 16:29.208
Rich!

16:29.291 --> 16:32.041
And it's mine, mine, mine!

16:32.750 --> 16:37.000
This should just about cover
the costs of your funerals.

16:37.083 --> 16:39.417
We're taking you for a ride...

16:39.500 --> 16:41.750
Travel, too? Better and better.

16:41.834 --> 16:44.917
And dropping you into the volcano.

16:45.000 --> 16:48.291
You're going to be deep-fried at dawn.

16:48.375 --> 16:52.375
Ha-ha-ha! Ha-ha-ha!

16:52.458 --> 16:53.750
[Rhino] Oh, boss.

16:58.458 --> 16:59.959
[Trader Moe] Sleep well, youse two.

17:00.041 --> 17:05.290
[Trader Moe] We want you nice and rested
for your swan dive into the volcano goo.

17:05.375 --> 17:07.000
I'm getting some shuteye.

17:07.083 --> 17:11.208
You slimes do something right for a change
and guard that money.

17:11.290 --> 17:12.541
Guard the money.

17:12.625 --> 17:14.208
<i>Ja</i>, we watch it, boss.

17:15.709 --> 17:18.625
First I have $50, but no,

17:18.709 --> 17:20.416
that wasn't good enough.

17:22.583 --> 17:25.040
I can't figure what went wrong.

17:25.125 --> 17:29.000
I know what went wrong. I trusted you!

17:29.083 --> 17:31.291
I'm sorry, kid.

17:31.792 --> 17:35.875
Oh, if only I hadn't busted
my boogie-woogie record.

17:35.959 --> 17:41.709
[scat singing]

17:44.458 --> 17:47.667
Oh, baby. Getting me an idea.

17:47.750 --> 17:50.417
Whetever it is, I don't like it already.

17:50.500 --> 17:54.083
[scat singing]

17:54.166 --> 17:56.667
[knocking] Now who could that be?

17:56.750 --> 18:01.583
[Baloo] Hello? Yes? Why thank you.

18:01.667 --> 18:02.667
I say...

18:02.750 --> 18:06.375
<i>♪ Scat gadda wadda wadda scat dat-doo...</i>
<i>Scat wadda wadda ♪</i>

18:06.458 --> 18:07.959
Well, now...

18:08.041 --> 18:09.333
Looky here.

18:09.375 --> 18:12.709
It's a telegram for the goons.

18:12.792 --> 18:17.500
Hey, you guys have just won
a free dancing lesson.

18:17.583 --> 18:19.625
-[Rhino] Free!
-[Gorilla] Ooh, no money!

18:19.709 --> 18:22.375
Yup, as an extra bonus,

18:22.458 --> 18:27.000
it's taught by that toe-tapping
boogie-woogie bear, me!

18:27.083 --> 18:29.625
-[Rhino] Oh, boy.
-[Gorilla] Boogie-woogie, <i>ja.</i>

18:36.125 --> 18:37.875
Baloo, what are you trying to--

18:37.959 --> 18:39.750
Ready? Here we go!

18:39.834 --> 18:43.125
Uh-one, uh-two, uh-one, two, three, four!

18:43.208 --> 18:45.000
Ha-ha-ha!

18:45.083 --> 18:47.125
[Rhino] Look, we dancing!

18:47.208 --> 18:49.875
[Gorilla] Boogie-woogie. I do so bad!

18:49.959 --> 18:52.333
What's going on here?

18:53.083 --> 18:54.667
[Rhino] You dance, too, boss.

18:54.750 --> 18:57.333
[Gorilla] <i>Ja</i>, boogie dance, boss.

18:58.083 --> 19:00.542
[Trader Moe] Will you put me down, you--

19:00.625 --> 19:01.625
[crash]

19:03.083 --> 19:05.041
Now, please don't get up.

19:05.125 --> 19:08.041
You guys just sit this one out.

19:14.041 --> 19:17.083
Ah, Baloo. That was great!

19:17.166 --> 19:20.375
Thanks, kid.
But we're not out of the woods yet.

19:23.583 --> 19:25.875
You wretchedheads!

19:25.959 --> 19:26.959
Get 'em!

19:37.542 --> 19:38.709
Get to the Sea Duck.

19:38.792 --> 19:40.208
Rev her up!

19:47.542 --> 19:48.917
Hurry, Baloo!

19:49.041 --> 19:52.375
I'm hurrying. I'm hurrying.

19:58.959 --> 20:02.166
You need a miracle
to get out of here alive.

20:02.959 --> 20:05.417
Uh, which could be arranged.

20:05.500 --> 20:09.792
Just what do miracles
go for around here, ol' buddy?

20:11.000 --> 20:13.834
Well, uh... [whispering]

20:13.917 --> 20:17.166
What? Oh, that's dockside robbery!

20:17.250 --> 20:19.166
Hey, take it or leave it, man.

20:21.750 --> 20:23.583
I'll take it.

20:23.667 --> 20:25.458
Baloo! Come on!

20:29.959 --> 20:31.458
Now, let's get out of here!

20:36.375 --> 20:37.959
We'll blast them out of the sky!

20:38.041 --> 20:39.291
Yeah, boom-boom.

20:39.375 --> 20:40.792
I like that.

20:44.709 --> 20:46.792
Yee-ha!

20:50.959 --> 20:52.667
Mmm-mwa!

20:58.291 --> 21:02.250
That is the hardest easy money
I've ever made in my life.

21:02.333 --> 21:03.875
I've been afraid to ask,

21:03.959 --> 21:07.041
did we escape with anything more
than our lives?

21:09.375 --> 21:11.959
Yeah... A hundred bucks.

21:12.041 --> 21:14.458
Double your money, like I promised.

21:14.542 --> 21:16.250
Hey, that's great!

21:16.333 --> 21:18.750
Thanks, Baloo. The rest is yours.

21:18.834 --> 21:21.166
Don't mention it, kid.

21:28.333 --> 21:29.583
[Kit] How's it going, Papa Bear?

21:29.667 --> 21:33.250
Oh, this working stuff's not <i>that </i> bad.

21:34.709 --> 21:38.041
Worst thing about it,
it hasn't got a beat.

21:39.458 --> 21:41.291
[boogie-woogie plays]

21:41.375 --> 21:43.458
Oh, yeah.

21:43.542 --> 21:45.250
[scat singing]

21:45.333 --> 21:48.667
Hey, you're playing my song!

21:48.750 --> 21:51.083
Surprise! Ha-ha!

21:51.166 --> 21:53.250
That's what I needed the 100 bucks for.

21:53.959 --> 21:59.583
Aw, kid... You-- ha-ha-ha.

22:01.208 --> 22:02.375
Oh, no.

22:03.291 --> 22:06.500
Baloo! Turn it down!

22:06.583 --> 22:08.542
Oh, Baloo.

